peruṅkōppeṇṭu tīppāyvāḷ colliyatu - tuṟai āṉantappaiyuḷ
</p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN246">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>palcāṉ ṟīrē palcāṉ ṟīrē</l>
<l>celkeṉac collā toḻikeṉa vilakkum</l>
<l>pollāc cūḻccip palcāṉ ṟīrē</l>
<l>yaṇilvari koṭuṅkāy vāḷpōḻn tiṭṭa</l>
<l>kāḻpō ṉalviḷar naṟuney tīṇṭā</l>
<l>taṭaiyiṭaik kiṭanta kaipiḻi piṇṭam</l>
<l>veḷḷeṭ cāntoṭu puḷippey taṭṭa</l>
<l>vēḷai ventai valci yākap</l>
<l>paraṟpey paḷḷip pāyiṉṟu vatiyu</l>
<l>muyavaṟ peṇṭirē mallē mātō</l>
<l>peruṅkāṭṭup paṇṇiya karuṅkōṭ ṭīma</l>
<l>numakkari tākuka tilla vemakkem</l>
<l>peruntōṭ kaṇavaṉ māynteṉa varumpaṟa</l>
<l>vaḷḷita ḻaviḻnta tāmarai</l>
<l>naḷḷirum poykaiyun tīyumō raṟṟē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1"> You who are worthy of much [praise], you who are worthy of much [praise], </l>
<l>with bad counsel, who block block [me], saying “stay behind”, </l>
<l>without saying “you may go”, you who are worthy of much [praise]: (2f.)</l>
<l corresp="10">are we not women capable of surviving/suffering women </l>
<l corresp="9">who as of today remain on mats/without mats as a bed, strewn with pebbles, </l>
<l corresp="8">while [our] food is something boiled of Vēḷai, </l>
<l corresp="7">that is cooked, pouring tamarind with a paste of white sesame </l>
<l corresp="6">on rice balls pressed with the hand which lie on a leaf, </l>
<l corresp="5">not touched by fragrant ghee, very white like the kernels </l>
<l corresp="4">that were cleaved by a sword from a curved unripe fruit striped [like] a squirrel? </l>
<l corresp="11">The pyre with [its] black peak prepared in the vast cremation ground, </l>
<l corresp="12">let it be difficult/precious for you. For us, </l>
<l corresp="13a-c">because our big-shouldered husband is gone, </l>
<l corresp="15a-c">the fire and the centre of the big pond </l>
<l>with lotuses that open [their] pointed petals so that the buds end (13c+14)</l>
<l corresp="15d">	are but one. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
